3.name: DeFi User
3.description: Users actively engaging with decentralized finance

confidence_metrics.confidence: How certain the model is about its categorization (0.0-1.0). Values around 0.60 are typical for addresses with limited transaction data. Higher values (0.80+) indicate strong evidence for the classification.

documentation.end_user_likelihood: Probability the address belongs to an individual (0.0-1.0). 0.70-1.00: HIGH likelihood of being an end user; 0.40-0.70: MEDIUM likelihood; 0.00-0.40: LOW likelihood (likely institutional/contract)

anomaly_detection.is_anomaly: Whether address shows unusual transaction patterns (true/false)
anomaly_detection.anomaly_score: The degree of abnormality (higher = more unusual)

documentation.investments: List of protocols/platforms the address has interacted with. Values indicate estimated proportion of portfolio.

transaction_patterns.total_transactions: Number of transactions for this address
transaction_patterns.unique_counterparties: Number of unique addresses interacted with
transaction_patterns.cluster_id: Which cluster the address belongs to. -1: Outlier (unique pattern); 0,1,2...: Specific cluster assignments
transaction_patterns.cluster_explanation: Human-readable description of the cluster

graph_metrics.pagerank: Importance of address in the network (0.0-1.0). Higher values indicate more central/influential addresses
graph_metrics.clustering_coefficient: How connected the address's neighbors are (0.0-1.0). 0.00: Neighbors don't transact with each other; 1.00: All neighbors transact with each other
graph_metrics.betweenness_centrality: How often this address acts as a bridge. Higher values indicate the address connects different parts of the network

behavior_patterns.gas_optimization: Evidence of waiting for low gas prices (0.0-1.0)
behavior_patterns.weekend_trading: Evidence of weekend activity (typical for retail) (0.0-1.0)
behavior_patterns.small_token_diversity: Evidence of holding few token types (0.0-1.0)
behavior_patterns.fiat_on_off_ramps: Evidence of using exchanges for fiat conversion (0.0-1.0)

temporal_patterns.weekend_ratio: Proportion of activity on weekends (0.0-1.0). 0.00: No weekend activity; 1.00: Only weekend activity
temporal_patterns.tx_time_entropy: Randomness of transaction timing. Lower values indicate more predictable patterns

automated_behavior.regular_intervals: Evidence of transactions at fixed intervals (0.0-1.0)
automated_behavior.bursty_activity: Evidence of bursts of activity followed by quiet (0.0-1.0)

suspicious_activities.wash_trading: Trading same assets back and forth

documentation.note: The 0.00 values are normal for addresses with limited transactions, as many metrics need multiple interactions to calculate meaningful values.
